/*

The city launched a Green Energy Rebate Program to encourage households to install solar panels. Each household is eligible for one rebate only, determined by a unique combination of house_no and street_name.

However, due to a bad UI on the government website, several applicants submitted duplicate applications from the same address—often believing theirs was the only one.

As part of the Municipal Audit, your task is to detect all duplicate addresses, and for each one, return a single summary line flagging the issue.

energy_rebate_applications:

id (intger): primary key
applicant_id (integer, unique): Unique ID for the application form
house_no (integer): Civic number
street_name (varchar): Street
Your query must return:

A single column named audit_note with one row per duplicated address, formatted like:

{N} applications (applicant_ids: ID1, ID2, ...) already filed at {house_no} {street_name}

Important: The applicant_ids inside each note must be listed in ascending order.

Notes:

Sort the final result by:
Number of applications (desc)
Street name (asc)
House number (asc)
For this sample data:

| applicant_id  | house_no | street_name      |
+---------------+----------+------------------+
| 1021          | 6        | Mc Gill Crst     |
| 1097          | 6        | Mc Gill Crst     |
| 1300          | 195      | Mc Gill Crst     |
| 1402          | 195      | Mc Gill Crst     |
| 101           | 12       | Elm St           |
| 107           | 12       | Elm St           |
| 112           | 12       | Elm St           |
| 4000          | 22       | Baker Street     |
Expected output is the followng:

| audit_note                                                                   |
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| 3 applications (applicant_ids: 101, 107, 112) already filed at 12 Elm St     |
| 2 applications (applicant_ids: 1021, 1097) already filed at 6 Mc Gill Crst   |
| 2 applications (applicant_ids: 1300, 1402) already filed at 195 Mc Gill Crst |


*/



SELECT
  COUNT(*) || ' applications (applicant_ids: '
    || STRING_AGG(applicant_id::text, ', ' ORDER BY applicant_id)
    || ') already filed at ' || house_no || ' ' || street_name AS audit_note
FROM energy_rebate_applications
GROUP BY house_no, street_name
HAVING COUNT(*) > 1
ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC,
         street_name ASC,
         house_no::int ASC;




